Thika is in Kiambu County, which on Sunday recorded 54 new Covid-19 infections. The Judiciary on Sunday announced the closure of the Thika Environment and Land Court, saying three staff members had tested positive for the coronavirus. 

In a statement, acting Chief Justice Philomena Mwilu said the three cases were found over the last 24 hours. 

"All urgent matters shall be directed to the Muranga Environment and Land Court," Justice Mwilu said. 



